The paper proposes a neural network architecture for financial time-series forecasting, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed architecture incorporates an attention mechanism that enables the layer to detect and focus on crucial temporal information, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of a large-scale dataset, which suggests the use of data science techniques (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on financial data analysis suggests the use of statistical and computational methods for financial applications (cs.SI).
